abstract: AOL will move its headquarters from Dulles, Va., next spring as tries to retool itself as an advertising company that competes with the likes of Google, Yahoo and Microsoft.
snippet: AOL will move its headquarters from Dulles, Va., next spring as tries to retool itself as an advertising company that competes with the likes of Google, Yahoo and Microsoft.
lead_paragraph: AOL will move its headquarters from its sprawling campus in Dulles, Va., to New York next spring as the online company tries to retool itself as an advertising company that competes with the likes of Google, Yahoo and Microsoft.

headline.main: AOL Moving Headquarters to New York

abstract: Powerset opens the kimono, a bit, hoping to turn skeptics into believers
snippet: Powerset opens the kimono, a bit, hoping to turn skeptics into believers
lead_paragraph: Powerset, a once-secretive, 70-person startup in San Francisco, has a problem: its goal to build a search engine that is both different and better than Google is so ambitious and improbable that it faces a large chorus of skeptics.
